                                java.lang.String iconPath)
        Constructor.
        Parameters:
        typeIdentifier - Type identifier of the configuration.
        configurationClass - Class of the configuration.
        componentInterface - The interface of the measurement component which is created when the configuration is compiled.
        typeName - Human readable name for this configuration.
        configurationClassification - Classification of configuration. This classification can e.g. be used to order configurations into a certain folder structure.
        iconPath - Path to an icon representing this configuration. This path should be a valid path to a resource, i.e. an icon saved inside a jar file loaded by YouScope.

      • getConfigurationClass

        public java.lang.Class<C> getConfigurationClass()
        Description copied from interface: ComponentMetadata
        Returns the class of the configuration of the measurement component. The class should have a public no-argument constructor, such that newInstance() can be called.
        Specified by:
        getConfigurationClass in interface ComponentMetadata<C extends Configuration>
        Returns:
        Configuration class of component.

      • getComponentInterface

        public java.lang.Class<? extends Component> getComponentInterface()
        Description copied from interface: ComponentMetadata
        Returns the interface of the measurement component created when the configuration is parsed. This should not be the implementation of the component, but rather a public interface implementing Remote.
        Specified by:
        getComponentInterface in interface ComponentMetadata<C extends Configuration>
        Returns:
        Component interface.
